<p>Congratulations. I would say Davis, Central, Inman in that order. Inman isn&#8217;t really all that close to the T. Personally, I would lean towards Central&#8212;-you could live in the big converted factory where I think (but you&#8217;d have to check&#8212;there&#8217;s a plaque) the Triscuit was invented, but its a bit seedier (okay, a lot) than Davis. If money was no object I&#8217;d try to find a place near Boston Common.</p>

