</div><div id="c4840">

<p>Congrats!</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://www.briandonovan.info" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=4840">brian donovan</a> at April 17, 2005 02:18 PM <a href="001679#c4840">#</a></p>

</div><div id="c4845">

<p>Congratulations, and I would recommend Davis Square.  I live pretty close to Davis (in East Arlington, in a place just like VisiCalc HQ) and it&#8217;s got a lot of nice restaurants and coffee shops where you can hang out and ogle other young interesting people.  If you&#8217;re visiting again to look for apartments and want a tour or guest bed, let me know.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://rura.org/shimon" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=4845">Shimon Rura</a> at April 18, 2005 11:52 AM <a href="001679#c4845">#</a></p>

</div><div id="c4853">

<p>Davis Square is pretty vibrant (it has its own <a href="http://www.livejournal.com/community/davis_square/">LiveJournal Community</a>) and very convenient to the red line.  That said, I&#8217;ve been living and working in an apartment in Inman for the last 2-1/2 years, and I&#8217;m very happy with the area.  It&#8217;s a cozy neighborhood with several good restaurants and straightforward bus service to Porter, Harvard, Davis, Central (all on the red line), Sullivan (orange line), and Lechmere (decent mall with Apple store).  And Central Square is only a 15 minute walk away.</p>

<p>Central has more stores and night life, but it&#8217;s also a lot sketchier than Davis and Inman.</p>

<p>Anyway, congratulations, and good luck with the apartment hunt!</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://retrovirus.com" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=4853">Joe Hughes</a> at April 20, 2005 09:49 PM <a href="001679#c4853">#</a></p>

</div><div id="c4863">

<p>Heh. &#8216;Life moves pretty fast. If you don&#8217;t stop and look around once and awhile you could miss it.&#8217; Good luck!</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://robertbrook.com" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=4863">Robert Brook</a> at April 22, 2005 08:43 AM <a href="001679#c4863">#</a></p>

</div>

